Reactor Kafka provides several interfaces for Kafka producers (senders). 

Consume and send data as a stream
-

`&lt;T&gt; Flux&lt;SenderResult&lt;T&gt;&gt; send(Publisher&lt;? extends SenderRecord&lt;K, V, T&gt;&gt; records)`


In this case we create `kafkaOutboundStream` by consuming messages from source topic and pass it to `kafkaSender.send()` that subscribes to this `Flux` and sends messages to Kafka. 

In this case we can apply processing logic before or after sending data to Kafka. In the following `processRecord` is applied before. 


```
Flux&lt;SenderResult&lt;ReceiverOffset&gt;&gt; transform() {
    Flux&lt;SenderRecord&lt;String, String, ReceiverOffset&gt;&gt; kafkaOutboundStream = kafkaReceiver.receive()
            .flatMap(sourceRecord -&gt;
                    processRecord(sourceRecord)
                            .map(resultRecord -&gt; SenderRecord.create(
                                    new ProducerRecord&lt;&gt;(&quot;destination-topic&quot;, sourceRecord.key(), resultRecord),
                                    sourceRecord.receiverOffset())
                            )
            );

    return kafkaSender.send(kafkaOutboundStream)
            .doOnNext(sourceRecord -&gt; sourceRecord.correlationMetadata().acknowledge());
}

private Mono&lt;String&gt; processRecord(ReceiverRecord&lt;String, String&gt; sourceRecord) {
    String transformed = sourceRecord.value().toUpperCase();
    return save(transformed)
            .thenReturn(transformed);
}
```


Consume and send data as multiple streams (fun-out)
-

In case we want to send data to Kafka and save to database in parallel, we would need to &quot;fan-out&quot; source `Flux` to consume and process it in parallel by 2 different subscriptions.


```
Flux&lt;Tuple2&lt;SenderResult&lt;ReceiverOffset&gt;, String&gt;&gt; transform() {
    Flux&lt;ReceiverRecord&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; source = kafkaReceiver.receive()
            .publish()
            .autoConnect(2);

    var kafkaOutboundStream = source
            .map(sourceRecord -&gt; SenderRecord.create(
                    new ProducerRecord&lt;&gt;(&quot;destination-topic&quot;, sourceRecord.key(), sourceRecord.value().toUpperCase()),
                    sourceRecord.receiverOffset())
            );

    var kafkaSenderStream = kafkaSender.send(kafkaOutboundStream);

    var dbSaveStream = source
            .flatMap(sourceRecord -&gt; save(sourceRecord.value().toUpperCase()));

    return Flux.zip(kafkaSenderStream, dbSaveStream)
            .doOnNext(resultRecord -&gt; resultRecord.getT1().correlationMetadata().acknowledge());
}

```

In this case you would need to `acknowledge` record when both operations are completed.


Consume and send data record by record
--

`KafkaOutbound&lt;K, V&gt; createOutbound().send(Publisher&lt;? extends ProducerRecord&lt;K, V&gt;&gt; records)`

As an alternative, you can process data and send to kafka using `kafkaSender.createOutbound().send()` that is more close to the code you shared.

```
Flux&lt;Tuple2&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; transform2() {
    return kafkaReceiver.receive()
            .flatMap(sourceRecord -&gt; {
                String transformed = sourceRecord.value().toUpperCase();
                var resultRecord = new ProducerRecord&lt;&gt;(&quot;destination-topic&quot;, sourceRecord.key(), transformed);
                return Mono.zip(sendToTopic(resultRecord), save(transformed))
                        .doOnNext(rec -&gt; sourceRecord.receiverOffset().acknowledge());
            });

}

private Mono&lt;String&gt; sendToTopic(ProducerRecord&lt;String, String&gt; message) {
    return kafkaSender.createOutbound()
            .send(Mono.just(message))
            .then()
            .thenReturn(message.value());
}
```

